        <h2>Docker & Containerization</h2>

        <h3>Docker Fundamentals</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Images vs Containers:</strong> Images are blueprints, containers are running instances</li>
            <li><strong>Dockerfile Best Practices:</strong>
                <pre># Multi-stage build for Django app
FROM python:3.11-slim as builder

WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --user --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

FROM python:3.11-slim

WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=builder /root/.local /root/.local
COPY . .

ENV PATH=/root/.local/bin:$PATH
ENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1

EXPOSE 8000
CMD ["gunicorn", "config.wsgi:application", "--bind", "0.0.0.0:8000"]</pre>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Docker Commands:</strong>
                <pre># Build image
docker build -t vuln-platform:latest .

# Run container
docker run -d -p 8000:8000 --name web vuln-platform:latest

# Execute command in running container
docker exec -it web python manage.py migrate

# View logs
docker logs -f web

# Stop and remove
docker stop web && docker rm web</pre>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Docker Compose</h3>
        <pre># docker-compose.yml
version: '3.8'

services:
  web:
    build: .
    ports:
      - "8000:8000"
    environment:
      - DATABASE_URL=mysql://user:pass@db:3306/vuln_db
      - REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379/0
    depends_on:
      - db
      - redis
    volumes:
      - ./app:/app
  
  db:
    image: mysql:8.0
    environment:
      MYSQL_DATABASE: vuln_db
      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: secret
    volumes:
      - mysql_data:/var/lib/mysql
  
  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine
    ports:
      - "6379:6379"
  
  celery:
    build: .
    command: celery -A config worker -l info
    depends_on:
      - db
      - redis

volumes:
  mysql_data:</pre>

        <h3>Container Optimization</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Use Alpine images for smaller size</li>
            <li>Multi-stage builds to reduce final image size</li>
            <li>.dockerignore file to exclude unnecessary files</li>
            <li>Layer caching - order commands by change frequency</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>AWS Cloud Services</h2>

        <h3>Core AWS Services</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>EC2:</strong> Virtual servers
                <ul>
                    <li>Instance types (t3, m5, c5)</li>
                    <li>Auto Scaling Groups</li>
                    <li>Elastic Load Balancer (ALB vs NLB)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>ECS/EKS:</strong> Container orchestration
                <ul>
                    <li>ECS: AWS-managed Docker orchestration</li>
                    <li>EKS: Managed Kubernetes</li>
                    <li>Fargate: Serverless containers</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>RDS:</strong> Managed relational databases
                <ul>
                    <li>MySQL, PostgreSQL</li>
                    <li>Read replicas for scaling</li>
                    <li>Automated backups and snapshots</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>S3:</strong> Object storage
                <ul>
                    <li>Storage classes (Standard, IA, Glacier)</li>
                    <li>Versioning and lifecycle policies</li>
                    <li>Static website hosting</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Lambda:</strong> Serverless compute
